        public static void assertLine2DEquals(Line2DReadOnly expected,
                                      Line2DReadOnly actual,
                                      double epsilon)
        Asserts on a per component basis that the two line 2Ds are equal to an epsilon.

        Note: the two arguments are considered to be equal if they are both equal to null.

        Parameters:
        expected - the expected line 2D. Not modified.
        actual - the actual line 2D. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance to use.
        Throws:
        java.lang.AssertionError - if the two line 2Ds are not equal. If only one of the arguments is equal to null.
